      "content": "i just feel like people don't get it. they think \"safety\" means more doctors and more pills, but that's just more of the same cage. to me, true peace doesn't look like \"managing\" the pain, it looks like the absence of it. like, if the only way to find stillness is to not be here anymore, isn't that just a kinder way to look at it? isn't there a kind of mercy in realizing when something is just beyond repair?",
